<subSubSection id="6C77424592FDEA8AE07BABCA2725F6DC" lastPageId="195" lastPageNumber="196" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="description">
<paragraph id="EFBEC6871A1AEEA58716DAD3AC6A46DD" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBDAC12AE681BEEE7D549538B7F27214" lastPageId="195" lastPageNumber="196" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">
Small tree 2-4 m tall with somewhat tetragonal and ridged stems in newer branches that are moderately to densely brown scurfy with stalked stellulate hairs; the nodal line present but inconspicuous. Petiole 0.3-4 cm. Leaf blade 17-43 
<normalizedToken id="BA99AB6CF08CCA2CAA5016A74B71FA97" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-14 cm, 5(-7) plinerved, with the innermost pair of veins usually diverging from the midvein 2.5-6 cm above the base in opposite to alternate fashion, elliptic, the base gradually tapering to decurrent on the petiole or less commonly rounded to slightly cordate, the apex acuminate to long acuminate, the margin entire to undulate, the adaxial surface sparsely scurfy-pulverulent to glabrous, the abaxial surface moderately and deciduously scurfy-pulverulent on the secondary and higher order veins. Inflorescence a terminal panicle 4.4-11.2 cm long branched at the base, accessory branches absent, brown scurfy on the branches, subulate, bracteoles 0.3-0.75 
<normalizedToken id="4FA34A1A38398E10780CD272DC46F5DF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.5 mm, persistent, fused and forming a nodal collar or ridge. Pedicel 0.5-2 mm. 1.25-1.75 
<normalizedToken id="EE75B242A42F70CCCA8F49BE454E2236" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.25-1.75 mm, hypanthium campanulate, not constricted, deciduously scurfy-pulverulent. Flowers 5-merous, not calyptrate, flower buds ca. 0.3-0.5 
<normalizedToken id="7D9FA0575C68CED5E08B5D1B5D969ACC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.2 mm, calyx tube 0.2-0.3 mm long, calyx lobes depressed-triangular to undulate, 0.5 mm long but concealed and barely exceeded by the exterior subulate teeth, androecial fringe present and beset with glandular hairs. Petals 2.75-3.25 
<normalizedToken id="0F66DF14653AD4BE2121D684C8F71E27" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.75-1 mm, magenta, linear-oblong, spread 
<pageBreakToken id="CBE1289EA9B19F645919ABB1F4DA8678" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" start="start">ing</pageBreakToken>
an anthesis, the apex acute, glabrous, spreading an anthesis, the margin entire. Stamens 10, 2.25-2.75 mm, radially arranged around the style, the filaments 1.25-1.5 mm long, with a geniculation near the apex, white, anthers 1-1.25 0.25-0.4 mm, oblong, yellow, the pore ca. 0.1 mm wide, somewhat dorsally inclined. Ovary 5 locular, 3/4 to 4/5 inferior, glabrous apically. Style 3.5-4.25 mm long, curving towards the apex, distance from the anther pore to the stigma 1-1.5 mm, stigma truncate, ca. 0.35 mm wide. Berry 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="E2AF02F220E614204C1C0AD41E7049B9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, purple-black. Seeds 0.35-0.5 mm, pyramidate, smooth with verruculose angles.
</paragraph>
